text:
Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

I looked up into the sky. Am i just hearing things. I look around the park and dont see anyone else talking to bugs, so i must just be sick or tired maybe. I think to myself, "Oh great, am i delusional? Thats great, right before my first day of college im talking to bees. Just at that moment, the bug repeats again. "Your Majesty, what are your orders? I looked straight at the bee in the eyes and didnt know what to say. "You talking to me?". Was the first thing I could think of. The bee says nothing. Then a couple seconds later the bee repeats "Your Majesty, what are your orders?". "If you dont tell me your orders than I am going to worry about you". Why would this little tiny bee be worried about me, i dont get it? I just stood there looking at it and then i started laughing. "Your already my best friend and I can barely even see you." I said. "Your Majesty, please give me a name so that I know what to identify you as". Jordan, i told the bee. "Hey bee, you want to get out of here and hang out. You dont have to grand any of my orders, just be cool". I said. "Your Majesty, is that an order? To be cool?". asked the bee. I looked at the bee and said "dont call me majesty, call me Jordan".
